-- Rail Track Takes Equity Stake in Queensland Rail Group, Review Reports
-- Rebecca Keenan
-- 2010-07-08T21:24:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/rail-track-takes-equity-stake-in-queensland-rail-group-review-reports.html

          
          
             Australian Rail Track Corporation,
owned by the Australian government, has agreed to contribute an
undisclosed amount of equity to a A$4.85 billion bid by mining
companies to purchase Queensland Rail Ltd.â€™s coal tracks, the
Australian Financial Review reported.  
 The group of companies, including BHP Billiton Ltd. and Rio
Tinto Group., has agreed that Australian Rail Track will manage
the rail network if the bid is successful, the newspaper said.
The group has A$3.5 billion in equity with three banks
underwriting A$1.3 billion in debt, the newspaper said.  
